cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AL, cs.CG 

This paper deals with the problem of finding a virtual backbone in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the networking community. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of graph theory and approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of connected dominating sets and the presentation of an approximation algorithm also make cs.AL (Algorithms) a likely sub-category. Finally, the study of unit disk graphs and the approximation algorithm's performance on such graphs suggest that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) could also be a relevant sub-category.
